node.text:
The Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) turns 31 today. To mark the anniversary of this landmark law, we're spotlighting this video we made with @AccessibleTravelNYC in 2019. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
ID: In this video, Lakshmee Lachhman-Persad, founder of the website Accessible Travel NYC, highlights sightseeing in NYC for wheelchair users. Lakshmee accompanies her sister, Annie, a wheelchair user, around NYC along with their family, and explains how they get around and navigate a day out in the City.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
For more on accessible travel in NYC, visit nycgo.com/accessibility (link in bio).

#ADA31 #ADA #AccessibleNYC

node.title: How to Explore NYC with a Wheelchair

node.text:
This is the first episode of our new video series, "The Freedom To Be." It focuses on the Black surf community in the Rockaways, with perspectives on the experience from author and former journalist Diane Cardwell (@diane_cardwell), as well as Lou Harris, the CEO of the NYC chapter of the Black Surfing Association (@black_surfing_rockaway). 
⁠⁠
About "The Freedom To Be": This series is part of #TheBlackExperienceInNYC travel hub on NYCgo.com and highlights NYC's endless and often unexpected opportunities for Black subcultures and affinity groups—acknowledging the five boroughs' vibrant abundance of ideas and expressions. A celebration of the diversity within Black culture in NYC, #TheFreedomToBe also underscores the contributions of these communities and groups to NYC's dynamism.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Visit nycgo.com/theblackexperience for more (link in bio).⁠⁠
⁠⁠

Don't miss this Priceless® experience at @Mr.MistaOh_NYC during #NYCRestaurantWeek: let the chefs teach you how to make kimchi, then sit down to a barbecue dinner with soju pairing.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
It all happens August 8, but there's limited seating, and spots are filling up fast. Exclusively for @Mastercard® cardholders. Link in bio to reserve your seat.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
A little background: The Oh family moved from Busan, South Korea in 2005. Father and son Seungho Oh and Suby Oh (Mr. Oh and Mista Oh, respectively) work the kitchen, while Holly Oh Diamond works the front of house. Seungho Oh used to own a kimchi factory in Korea, and Suby Oh studied at Le Cordon Bleu in Portland, Oregon. Together this family team will bring you hospitality, culinary joy, and an intimate dining experience.⁠⁠
⁠⁠

It’s finally time to experience the five boroughs in real life again. #ItsTimeForNYC. ⁠⁠⁠
⁠⁠⁠
We've asked locals how they're spending their time in the City right now. Link in bio for A Fitness Fanatic's Guide to NYC by fitness instructor and actor Laura Giromini Arrigoni (@viverenewyork).⁠⁠
⁠⁠⁠
Laura's roster includes a lot of Brooklyn, a little Times Square, some pizza, Governors Island, and more. You can save her itinerary or create one of your own. And when you do, you can enter our sweepstakes for a chance to experience it in real life, plus a free trip for you and a friend.*⁠⁠⁠
⁠⁠⁠
Pictured: A video of Arrigoni exercising throughout NYC, including the Brooklyn Bridge; a pizza at Sottocasa in Brooklyn; Arrigoni in Times Square for the @TimesSquareNYC's bi-annual solstice yoga event; historic buildings on Governors Island. 📷: @viverenewyork⁠⁠

node.text:
In New York City, restaurants are more than just places to have a meal; they’re institutions, many charmingly unchanged since the decade they opened. Our #NYCRestaurantWeek Classics Collection celebrates these spots—like the Russian Tea Room, where Madonna worked before she was famous. ⁠
⁠
